WEBVTT

00:01.294 --> 00:02.875
LUCY:
Previously on Killjoys...

00:02.962 --> 00:06.671
I present Sylas and Evi Robbel
of Land Robbel,

00:06.757 --> 00:08.884
primary benefactors
of this prison.

00:08.968 --> 00:10.333
Ijust need you
to kill my brother.

00:10.428 --> 00:12.168
You're going to need this.
Thanks.

00:12.305 --> 00:14.512
I want Johnny Jaqobis
to go free.
You have a deal.

00:14.599 --> 00:16.590
This is why we needed
Dutch's DNA.

00:16.684 --> 00:17.764
So what did I miss?

00:17.852 --> 00:19.843
THE LADY:
What are you to me
if you don’t deliver?

00:19.937 --> 00:23.646
Either find Pree or find
someone who will burn
down the galaxy for him.

00:23.733 --> 00:26.099
We need to
wake up Westerley.
Yeah, starting with Gared.

00:26.194 --> 00:27.479
TU RIN: He’s safer in the dark.

00:27.570 --> 00:30.562
I'm in the middle
of a prison beef
with my old pal Coren Jeers.

00:30.656 --> 00:32.237
That little handoff
got us a chip.

00:32.742 --> 00:34.698
Johnny's got it to turn out
everyone's lights.

00:34.827 --> 00:38.035
lfyou help us,
yours stays on.
All right.

00:39.165 --> 00:40.200
This ship is ours.

00:40.291 --> 00:42.623
You lying piece of rat shit.

00:42.710 --> 00:45.247
COREN:
Now, we can really
settle the score.

00:48.257 --> 00:49.633
MAN: Move, move, move!

00:51.427 --> 00:52.792
(PRISONERS CLAMORING)

00:55.097 --> 00:56.303
We need to stay on task.

00:56.390 --> 00:58.381
That might be
a little bit tricky.

00:58.476 --> 01:01.468
So long as we survive
the next few hours,
nothing's changed.

01:01.562 --> 01:03.803
We still need the ship,
and Johnny still needs
to get the message out.

01:03.898 --> 01:04.933
Dutch.

01:06.234 --> 01:08.190
We don't even know
if he's still alive.

01:14.617 --> 01:17.359
Come on. Time for a walk.

01:22.708 --> 01:24.699
(CLANGING)
(ALARM BLARING)

01:35.346 --> 01:36.506
They're gone.

01:38.766 --> 01:42.634
You asshole.
You hijacked my ship!

01:42.812 --> 01:47.101
Yeah, but then
Sparlo and Jeers
hijacked our hijack,

01:47.191 --> 01:50.354
so, you know,
it's kind of a wash.

01:51.279 --> 01:54.146
Right now, we need to
get you somewhere safe
and get that looked at.

01:54.240 --> 01:56.526
But you're still
my prisoner.

01:56.617 --> 01:58.653
Look, there are cons
running around
looking for targets.

01:58.744 --> 02:01.577
And a warden?
That's about the
primest one they can find.

02:02.206 --> 02:04.538
So unless you wanna take
your chance with them,

02:05.501 --> 02:06.957
who else are
you gonna trust?

02:09.171 --> 02:12.299
(PRISONERS CLAMORING)
(CLANGING)

02:14.051 --> 02:17.088
You're not so tough
without the masks
and the cuffs now,

02:17.179 --> 02:18.555
huh, assholes?

02:19.557 --> 02:21.047
SYLAS:
Please just let me go.

02:21.976 --> 02:23.512
D'AVIN: I'm not seeing
the other Qreshi.

02:24.812 --> 02:28.771
If she's lucky,
they killed her fast.

02:32.236 --> 02:33.521
(CHUCKLES)

02:35.156 --> 02:36.862
Welcome to the party.

02:37.867 --> 02:39.573
How do I look?

02:39.994 --> 02:43.031
You should have
heard the crowd when
we strung up this shitbag.

02:44.832 --> 02:46.197
Shh, Shh, Shh.

02:48.794 --> 02:52.833
Can you imagine the screams
when I hang a Killjoy?
(LAUGHS)

02:52.965 --> 02:55.957
Coren! What the hells
are you doing?

02:56.052 --> 02:58.213
Ah, relax, Sparliecakes.

02:58.304 --> 03:00.465
Just taking care of some
personal business.

03:00.556 --> 03:04.515
Then we ransom this one
back to his family

03:04.602 --> 03:06.684
and roll in the joy.

03:06.771 --> 03:07.886
Ransom?
Mmm.

03:07.980 --> 03:09.015
We're supposed
to take the ship

03:09.106 --> 03:10.687
and get the hells
out of the J,
that was the deal.

03:10.775 --> 03:12.561
Now I'm changing the deal.
Shocker

03:12.651 --> 03:13.982
Shutupl

03:18.282 --> 03:22.275
Meanwhile, we saw
the Warden and the other
Killjoy on the CCTV,

03:22.370 --> 03:23.860
so they gotta be
around somewhere.

03:23.954 --> 03:25.865
(GASPS) Why don't
you be useful
and go find them?

03:25.956 --> 03:28.368
I'm not your lackey, Jeers.
I'm your partner.

03:28.459 --> 03:30.871
You are what I say you are.
That's not the deal!

03:30.961 --> 03:32.622
(OTHERS CLAMORING)

03:36.759 --> 03:38.750
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:39.553 --> 03:40.542
Ooh, ooh

03:42.181 --> 03:43.341
Ooh, ooh

03:44.600 --> 03:47.012
Ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh

03:48.437 --> 03:49.552
Ooh, ooh

03:51.774 --> 03:53.810
MAN ON PA:
Toxins can be anywhere.

03:53.901 --> 03:57.314
Decon showers
are always nearby.

03:57.405 --> 03:59.487
Keep your family safe.

03:59.573 --> 04:02.030
Decon shower just in case.

04:06.789 --> 04:10.281
I can't believe...
it's all a lie.

04:11.001 --> 04:12.377
It's a lot.

04:13.963 --> 04:17.000
I don't think
I can do this.
But you must.

04:17.091 --> 04:18.672
For him.

04:19.135 --> 04:21.626
The Lady's after
anyone who's awake.

04:21.720 --> 04:23.972
They've destroyed
millions ofjoy
in property,

04:24.056 --> 04:25.466
and we know they got
their information
from him.

04:25.558 --> 04:27.048
No. He would've
told me all this.

04:28.018 --> 04:31.351
He hates it when I lie.
Then why is Pree
lying to you?

04:31.981 --> 04:34.393
He's been awake
this whole time
without telling you.

04:35.568 --> 04:37.479
Next time
you see him,

04:37.570 --> 04:40.152
I want you
to swap this
for his ID badge.

04:40.239 --> 04:41.274
What is it?

04:41.949 --> 04:44.565
It's a way for us to know
where he's going,
who he's talking to.

04:45.369 --> 04:47.325
lfyou can help me
do this cleanly,

04:47.413 --> 04:49.278
I can get you both
out of the Quad.

04:49.582 --> 04:52.119
And don't think of it
as betraying
the rebellion.

04:52.209 --> 04:55.576
Think of it
as your last chance
to save Pree,

04:55.921 --> 04:58.503
because believe me,
it is.

05:02.845 --> 05:05.086
We're leaving the Quad.
We are getting a ransom!

05:05.598 --> 05:06.678
Coren's right.

05:06.765 --> 05:10.223
You've got 4,000 prisoners
who are knocked out
by their chips.

05:10.311 --> 05:11.721
When they wake up,
how are you gonna
feed them?

05:11.812 --> 05:13.313
How are you gonna
keep them in line?
Huh?

05:14.273 --> 05:15.558
You need money.

05:15.649 --> 05:17.355
You need to get
the Qreshis back
to their people,

05:17.443 --> 05:18.558
or they'll never
stop chasing you.

05:19.862 --> 05:22.228
Well, thank you,
Yardeen.

05:22.990 --> 05:24.150
I'll kill you faster.

05:24.241 --> 05:26.493
There's still
a problem, Coren.

05:26.577 --> 05:30.536
Why the hells would
the Qreshis come
to negotiate on a ship

05:30.623 --> 05:33.114
that's just been
taken over by a bunch
of lunatic convicts?

05:33.209 --> 05:34.699
Who says
we're lunatics?

05:36.712 --> 05:38.452
Oh, well, okay.

05:38.547 --> 05:40.333
You need
a cover story,
like,

05:40.424 --> 05:43.166
the Warden lost control
of one wing during
the Bellaxion.

05:43.260 --> 05:44.716
Her Qreshi guests
were taken

05:44.803 --> 05:46.930
and she doesn't
want to come in
guns blazing

05:47.014 --> 05:49.847
until the Qreshis are out
safely, so she'll negotiate
for their return.

05:49.934 --> 05:51.174
That actually makes sense.

05:51.268 --> 05:52.804
Except we don't
have the Warden.

05:52.895 --> 05:55.637
No, you don't.
But you have me.

05:55.898 --> 05:58.810
You? Why would
I trust you?

05:58.901 --> 06:00.641
Because I'm a Killjoy.

06:00.736 --> 06:02.601
And I dealt with
Qreshis every day.

06:03.489 --> 06:06.606
And I know how
to play them and win.

06:11.622 --> 06:13.032
What do you say?

06:13.123 --> 06:14.454
Partner?

06:18.045 --> 06:20.206
JAQ: Weren't you scared
when the Green was dying?

06:20.297 --> 06:24.836
Yes. Papa, he said
there was one place
I would be safe.

06:24.927 --> 06:27.009
So he put me back
in a cube.

06:28.889 --> 06:32.802
But then, you found me.

06:32.893 --> 06:35.930
Now, we need to sneak back
into the Quad to save my dad.

06:36.855 --> 06:38.766
We're gonna need money
for passage.

06:38.857 --> 06:41.599
Why would
we need money?

06:41.694 --> 06:43.525
Capitalism.
Long story.

06:43.612 --> 06:46.228
Jaq, why don't you
go on up ahead?

06:46.323 --> 06:47.358
Okay.

06:49.076 --> 06:50.316
Ithink
I like him.

06:50.869 --> 06:52.951
He's got
your stubbornness.

06:53.497 --> 06:54.657
And I'm just
putting it out there,

06:54.748 --> 06:56.659
but we needed
Dutch's DNA
to open the cube,

06:56.750 --> 07:01.414
and that involved
some kissing...
But I didn't enjoy it.

07:01.505 --> 07:03.291
Liar.
Fine, a little.

07:04.174 --> 07:05.880
But only because
I missed you.

07:06.760 --> 07:09.217
I got here
as soon as I could.

07:10.431 --> 07:13.639
I promised you
an empire, remember?

07:13.726 --> 07:16.763
I guess we'd better
hurry up and save
the universe together.

07:17.146 --> 07:18.431
Tick, tock.

07:23.861 --> 07:26.398
You're human?

07:26.488 --> 07:28.194
You're still Hullen.

07:29.116 --> 07:30.322
How?

07:31.160 --> 07:32.400
JAQ: Come on,
keep up.

07:41.879 --> 07:44.837
ANEELA: So,
what about this money?

07:45.007 --> 07:46.872
JAQ: Uncle Johnny
taught me some
of his old cons

07:46.967 --> 07:48.832
back when we were on Telen.

07:49.970 --> 07:52.086
JOHN:
I'm just glad that
we found this wand.

07:52.640 --> 07:53.925
Cons took all the pain meds.

07:54.016 --> 07:55.756
They're probably having
a big old party in G wing.

07:55.851 --> 07:57.682
Yet again,
thanks to you.

07:57.770 --> 07:59.431
NEWCY: Actually,
it was thanks to me.

07:59.521 --> 08:01.682
What the hells is that?
No, relax, relax.

08:02.441 --> 08:06.309
Newcy, meet Warden Rennika.
Rennika, meet Newcy.

08:06.403 --> 08:09.987
Hello. / am a multi-threaded
neuro-coded Al.

08:10.074 --> 08:12.360
/ live in Johnny’s pocket.
Yes, you do.

08:12.451 --> 08:15.318
How the hells
did you get that
into my prison?

08:15.412 --> 08:17.323
I made it from
one of your guard's
wrist controllers.

08:17.414 --> 08:18.870
lt's, um...
It's kind of my thing.

08:19.375 --> 08:21.787
And... good as new.

08:22.711 --> 08:24.292
Now, ifyou wanna
show me some gratitude,

08:24.380 --> 08:25.961
I need to get eyes
and ears on my partners

08:26.048 --> 08:27.254
and send a message
to Westerley.

08:27.341 --> 08:28.421
PRISONER: Hey,
what the hells
are you doing?

08:30.552 --> 08:32.634
Oh, thank the trees!
It's a warden.

08:32.721 --> 08:35.133
You son of a bitch.
She's wounded.

08:35.224 --> 08:37.010
You gotta watch her
and I'm gonna
go tell Coren.

08:37.101 --> 08:40.218
VVaH,no,no,no,no.
Why don't I tell Coren
and you watch her?

08:40.312 --> 08:42.177
I'm not letting you
take the credit
for this.

08:43.148 --> 08:44.854
Okay, fine, but at least
leave me a gun

08:44.942 --> 08:46.773
so no other assholes
will take her from me.

08:46.860 --> 08:48.020
Fine.

08:51.490 --> 08:54.482
Now, we have a gun.

08:54.910 --> 08:55.990
Hmm.

08:56.370 --> 08:58.235
COMPUTER: Searching for
communication channel.

08:58.330 --> 09:00.116
All right, hurry up
and call the Qreshi.

09:00.249 --> 09:02.114
Not before you hear
what I have to say.
I'm not interested.

09:02.209 --> 09:03.415
In getting out
of this alive?

09:03.836 --> 09:05.372
Coren and l have
an understanding.

09:05.462 --> 09:08.329
Well, then you're
an even bigger idiot
than I thought.

09:08.424 --> 09:10.005
Again with the sweet talk.

09:10.092 --> 09:12.799
Do you really think
that the Qreshis
are gonna pay up

09:12.886 --> 09:14.001
andletyouleave?

09:14.096 --> 09:16.428
And even if they
don't get you,
what's stopping Coren

09:16.515 --> 09:19.598
from cutting your throat
the minute he has
what he wants?

09:21.270 --> 09:22.806
Here's a better idea.

09:23.355 --> 09:26.597
I give back the hostages.
No ransom, no questions.

09:28.610 --> 09:30.066
You take out Coren.

09:31.155 --> 09:35.569
And then, we go home
to Westerley.

09:36.201 --> 09:37.816
There's no
going home for me.

09:37.911 --> 09:39.287
Maybe not as a criminal.

09:40.164 --> 09:41.700
But what about as a hero?

09:41.790 --> 09:43.326
COMPUTER: Incoming call.

09:43.959 --> 09:45.244
(MACHINE BUZZING)

09:56.263 --> 09:59.505
This is Captain Pike
of Land Robbel.
Who’s this?

09:59.600 --> 10:02.763
This is Warden Rennika
of the Herks Supermax
Prison Cruiser.

10:05.272 --> 10:07.308
We've got a bit
of a problem here.

10:07.399 --> 10:09.776
We ain't got a hold
of the Robbel girl yet.

10:09.860 --> 10:11.100
Butwe will, Coren.

10:11.737 --> 10:12.772
Sure.

10:13.155 --> 10:16.192
But ifyou actually
want her back alive,
let me find her.

10:16.283 --> 10:17.944
And you're gonna
do that how, exactly?

10:18.035 --> 10:19.696
She gave me
this signal receiver.

10:20.996 --> 10:24.113
I can reverse the broadcast,
track her back to
wherever she is.

10:24.208 --> 10:25.539
What?

10:25.626 --> 10:27.787
My brother's not the only one
who can mess with a gadget.

10:30.088 --> 10:32.704
Temet, you and the meathead
have an heiress to find.

10:32.800 --> 10:35.633
And lock up Little Lord
Pisspants in the
Warden's office.

10:35.719 --> 10:38.176
The whimpering is
harshing my vibe.

10:38.263 --> 10:40.049
Get up.
(GASPS) Ow!

10:41.183 --> 10:42.798
We need to do
this now, Sparlo.

10:42.893 --> 10:45.225
Not yet.
I want to enjoy this.

10:47.105 --> 10:48.766
Qreshi contingent's
on their way.

10:48.857 --> 10:51.473
Once they get here,
our people will be
in guard uniforms

10:51.568 --> 10:53.559
to escort them
to the Warden's office.

10:53.654 --> 10:56.691
Then we make the deal,
and we're gone.

10:57.241 --> 10:58.526
Fabulous.

10:59.660 --> 11:01.070
So I need her
to do the negotiating,

11:01.161 --> 11:03.652
and the other Killjoy's
finding the Qreshi.

11:03.747 --> 11:06.705
Really, the only person
I don't need anymore
is you, Sparlo.

11:13.882 --> 11:14.997
There.

11:16.677 --> 11:18.508
(LAUGHS)
Isn't that better?

11:24.226 --> 11:25.306
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

11:25.769 --> 11:28.431
What a weight
off my shoulder,
you know?

11:28.772 --> 11:30.933
Guess I never was
one for partnerships.

11:31.024 --> 11:33.310
Sparlo didn't deserve
to die like that.

11:33.485 --> 11:34.861
No, he didn't.

11:36.697 --> 11:39.655
But what's done is done,
and we need the ransom
to survive.

11:39.741 --> 11:41.697
Killjoy makes a lot
of sense, Mace.

11:41.785 --> 11:43.150
And I could always
use another
ﬁghthand.

11:44.955 --> 11:46.786
Mmm?
What do you say?

11:48.125 --> 11:50.616
What's next, boss?

11:50.878 --> 11:52.163
(CHUCKLES)

11:52.254 --> 11:56.714
Now, we get dressed
and go see some Qreshis
about a ransom.

11:56.925 --> 11:58.961
And lwasjust
getting used to
this cloak.

12:01.972 --> 12:03.212
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
(GRUNTS)

12:03.307 --> 12:04.888
So the closer we get,
the more it shocks you?

12:04.975 --> 12:06.181
Yes, pretty much.

12:06.268 --> 12:07.883
Thatdoesnt
seem like
a very good idea.

12:07.978 --> 12:09.388
Yeah, well,
it's a role
I'm used to.

12:09.479 --> 12:11.310
SYLAS:
Why did my sister
even give that to you?

12:11.398 --> 12:12.638
You don't wanna know.

12:12.733 --> 12:14.940
Oh, Gods, you're not one
of her sex slaves, are you?

12:15.027 --> 12:16.142
I mean, I can see it.
You've got Daddy's...

12:16.236 --> 12:17.442
She wanted me to kill you.

12:17.529 --> 12:18.689
What?

12:18.780 --> 12:20.941
How dare she?
I'm an Qreshi.

12:21.033 --> 12:23.945
She said you were
planning to kill her.

12:24.036 --> 12:26.493
(SCOFFS)
I would never.
Not recently.

12:26.663 --> 12:28.164
Well, here she is.

12:30.500 --> 12:31.910
(SHRIEKS)

12:34.338 --> 12:35.874
You had one job.

12:39.968 --> 12:41.083
What you thinking?

12:42.387 --> 12:45.595
| just wish that we
had jobs where we could
do this all the time.

12:45.682 --> 12:49.015
Well, there is.
Butwho'd be
paying who?

12:49.102 --> 12:51.559
No, I mean, being together.

12:52.314 --> 12:53.429
All the time.

12:55.984 --> 12:57.815
I think Cindy would have
something to say about that.

12:57.903 --> 12:59.268
I told her.

13:00.530 --> 13:01.781
About us.

13:02.658 --> 13:04.774
It's over.
You did?

13:04.868 --> 13:06.074
Yeah.

13:10.123 --> 13:11.863
(CHUCKLES)

13:12.793 --> 13:14.033
What brought this on?

13:14.127 --> 13:16.834
| just thought,
if I'm gonna have
a good life,

13:18.131 --> 13:20.508
I need to be honest
with the people in it.

13:20.801 --> 13:21.836
You know?

13:25.263 --> 13:26.673
(COMMUNICATOR BUZZES)

13:32.062 --> 13:33.177
Everything okay?

13:33.855 --> 13:35.231
Rainbows and sunshine.

13:35.649 --> 13:37.014
New warrant is in.

13:37.901 --> 13:39.562
I'm just gonna
go freshen up.

14:02.718 --> 14:05.004
And really, you should
just give me access
to everything.

14:05.095 --> 14:08.087
Just to be
on the safe side.
You can trust me.

14:09.891 --> 14:11.222
Pinky swear.

14:11.393 --> 14:12.633
(CLEARS THROAT)

14:13.770 --> 14:15.055
Mmm...

14:18.316 --> 14:20.773
There. Full and
complete access.

14:20.944 --> 14:23.777
Please don't make me
regret it any more
than I already do.

14:25.532 --> 14:28.444
Now, as soon as I find
my friends, I can figure
a way to stick

14:28.535 --> 14:30.366
a flaming hot rod
up Coren's...

14:30.537 --> 14:32.073
Well, hello, there.

14:32.164 --> 14:33.495
You have
a cloaking broadcaster?

14:33.582 --> 14:35.197
An honest-to-trees
cloaking broadcaster?

14:35.292 --> 14:37.578
That is so, so cool.
And illegal.

14:37.711 --> 14:39.747
Also cool.
Yeah, it came
with the Herks.

14:39.838 --> 14:42.454
She was
a smuggler's freighter
back in the day.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.881
But the engines
are such energy hogs,

14:44.968 --> 14:46.879
I had to decom everything
just to keep her airborne.

14:46.970 --> 14:48.210
Never took you for
a gearjunkie.

14:49.431 --> 14:51.046
lwasn't till I came
on the Herks.

14:51.141 --> 14:53.223
And warden is not
my firstjob.

14:53.310 --> 14:54.925
Oh, yeah, what were you?
Ah, let me guess.

14:55.437 --> 14:59.305
You clearly like authority,
yelling, uniforms.

15:00.358 --> 15:02.735
Gym teacher?
Psychiatrist.

15:02.944 --> 15:05.071
Huh. I wasn't expecting that.

15:05.155 --> 15:08.238
And what about you?
You always wanted
to be a Killjoy?

15:11.203 --> 15:13.114
Yeah, well, I...

15:13.205 --> 15:14.536
I did for a long time.

15:15.749 --> 15:16.989
(DOOR OPENING)

15:18.251 --> 15:19.286
Somebody's coming.

15:19.544 --> 15:21.284
Take cover.

15:33.600 --> 15:36.091
Is he one
of your guards?
No.

15:37.020 --> 15:38.760
What the hell
is he doing?

15:39.689 --> 15:43.227
Coren, there's no way
the Nine are gonna
pay a million joy.

15:43.318 --> 15:45.104
The Land Robbels
are just a small house.

15:45.195 --> 15:47.026
I don't care if they're
Badland scavengers.

15:47.114 --> 15:48.354
This is how you haggle.

15:48.448 --> 15:49.949
You start high and then
you work it out.

15:50.033 --> 15:51.273
Not with the Qreshi.

15:51.368 --> 15:53.450
They won't
think you're serious,
and shut it down.

15:53.578 --> 15:55.830
And how
do you know that?
I'm a Qreshi.

15:55.914 --> 15:57.245
Land Faresh.

15:57.958 --> 15:59.664
Every family has to have
a bad apple, right?

16:01.920 --> 16:03.126
COREN: Don't screw
this up, Killjoy.

16:03.213 --> 16:05.078
Yours isn't
the only life
on the line.

16:11.930 --> 16:13.090
Captain Pike.

16:13.181 --> 16:15.092
I wish we were meeting
under better circumstances.

16:15.684 --> 16:16.764
Same.

16:16.852 --> 16:19.594
You just look like
you took some hits
of your own during this.

16:21.231 --> 16:22.721
Yeah, it comes
with the territory.

16:23.733 --> 16:26.145
But what really matters now
is that the Robbels
are being held

16:26.236 --> 16:27.851
by the worst scum
on this ship.

16:29.322 --> 16:31.404
Real shitballs, and stupid.

16:31.533 --> 16:32.568
(MUFFLED PROTESTING)

16:32.659 --> 16:35.196
They're demanding a ransom
and safe passage
off this ship.

16:35.287 --> 16:37.744
My advice... Pay it.

16:38.957 --> 16:42.370
I'd like to know
how you lost control
of your own prison.

16:43.879 --> 16:45.915
Well, the Bellaxion
sure didn't help.

16:46.256 --> 16:48.087
It really riles up
the prisoners,

16:48.175 --> 16:50.632
especially having
a Qreshi champion
at the end.

16:50.719 --> 16:52.129
I always thought
it was a bad idea.

16:52.220 --> 16:54.131
To be honest,
so have I.

16:54.764 --> 16:56.379
But between this
and arms trading,

16:56.474 --> 16:59.511
the Robbels make good money
for a lot of nasty shit.

16:59.603 --> 17:02.310
I suppose now is time
to pay some of it back.

17:03.231 --> 17:05.768
How much
are the shitballs
demanding?

17:09.154 --> 17:11.019
One million joy,
but I'm sure you're not...

17:11.114 --> 17:12.274
Should be fine.

17:12.365 --> 17:14.651
Ijust need to contact
my people back home.

17:14.826 --> 17:15.941
Do you mind?

17:25.378 --> 17:26.538
Ha-ha! You see?

17:27.172 --> 17:28.628
Who knows Qreshis?

17:28.715 --> 17:30.831
No,no,no.
That was way too easy.
Mace, tell him.

17:30.926 --> 17:33.884
It's not my place
to tell the top dog
what to think.

17:34.012 --> 17:35.001
(SUCKS IN AIR)

17:35.096 --> 17:37.087
That's what loyalty
looks like, Killjoy.

17:39.142 --> 17:40.598
Something isn't right.

17:45.357 --> 17:46.938
Land Robbel, I think.

17:47.025 --> 17:48.356
Could be a rescue team.

17:49.402 --> 17:51.233
If that's a rescue team,

17:51.321 --> 17:52.982
then why did he just plant
a fusion bomb

17:53.073 --> 17:54.529
that could take out
half this ship?

18:00.956 --> 18:01.945
SYLAS: You look
a little tired, V.

18:02.040 --> 18:03.576
Is it from all the fratricide
you've been attempting?

18:03.667 --> 18:04.873
Mother said you
were a mistake.

18:04.960 --> 18:06.575
Mother told me you ate
your twin in the womb.

18:06.670 --> 18:08.786
Just sit
and shut up in
the corner, or else.

18:09.923 --> 18:11.788
I cannot believe that
you tried to kill me.

18:11.883 --> 18:13.089
Your own baby brother.

18:13.176 --> 18:14.916
Oh, don't act all high
and mighty, Sylas.

18:15.011 --> 18:16.592
You tried
to poison me
when l was eight.

18:16.680 --> 18:18.841
You got any gags?
You shut up and
sit down with them.

18:18.932 --> 18:20.092
SYLAS:
You know that
was Mother's idea?

18:20.684 --> 18:22.140
And even if
you had died,

18:22.227 --> 18:25.515
Uncle Anton would have taken
over Land Robbel until lwas
of age or married.

18:25.605 --> 18:28.096
(GASPS) So you have
been thinking about it.

18:28.775 --> 18:31.812
(SIGHS)
I hope John is
having fun at least.

18:32.362 --> 18:33.522
Okay.

18:34.030 --> 18:37.818
Now, you hold the trip switch
while I disengage the core.

18:39.160 --> 18:41.993
Careful. Careful.

18:42.080 --> 18:44.822
Okay, really
not as helpful
as you think.

18:47.085 --> 18:50.077
Three, two...

18:51.673 --> 18:52.662
One.

18:52.841 --> 18:53.921
(BEEPS)

18:54.217 --> 18:56.128
(BOTH SIGH IN RELIEF)

18:57.721 --> 19:00.133
Yeah, that's nice work.
Nice work, Killjoy.

19:00.223 --> 19:01.884
Please, "Johnny"
to my friends.

19:02.851 --> 19:04.716
Also "Mr. Amazing
Pants" works.

19:09.399 --> 19:10.764
All right,
come on.
Come on.

19:13.153 --> 19:14.268
Okay, I got it.

19:15.530 --> 19:16.815
Yes! There she is.

19:17.282 --> 19:19.489
Wait, those
are my clothes.

19:19.576 --> 19:21.612
What... Why is Yardeen
wearing my clothes?

19:21.703 --> 19:22.988
Special occasion? I...

19:23.079 --> 19:26.037
Ijust need to find a way
to tell her about these
Qreshi assholes.

19:26.124 --> 19:28.911
Newcy, can you tap into
the onboard comms system?

19:29.127 --> 19:31.743
NEWCY:
Of course, Johnny.
How do I do that?

19:31.880 --> 19:33.871
Justaccess
the mainframe
wirelessly.

19:33.965 --> 19:36.172
