incestuous milkmaids?

21:48.600 --> 21:51.137
Three for Qresh.
We'll take it
from there.

21:51.227 --> 21:52.512
The deal was two.

21:53.813 --> 21:55.349
Then the deal is wrong.

21:56.065 --> 21:57.930
Figure it out, ladies.
I'll be waiting.

21:58.902 --> 22:02.770
Kendry,
we need to talk.
Not here.

22:02.864 --> 22:05.776
You don't get to change
our plans without
consulting me.

22:05.867 --> 22:07.903
That's very
human of you.

22:07.994 --> 22:10.781
Wow, ifyou have
something to say, say it.
Mom?

22:10.872 --> 22:12.487
BOTH: Which one?

22:16.294 --> 22:19.411
You cheated.
We want our money back.

22:19.506 --> 22:22.418
Well, it's nice
to want things.

22:22.509 --> 22:24.716
But cards is
a game of chance.
We were just lucky.

22:24.802 --> 22:27.214
Bullshit. I saw this one.

22:27.972 --> 22:31.260
Whispering in your ear
before every damn round.

22:31.351 --> 22:34.218
You seemed to know every time
what we were gonna play.

22:34.312 --> 22:35.427
lcachatcheaﬂng.

22:35.522 --> 22:37.888
And I call this
refunding you
your whole ass.

22:38.024 --> 22:39.139
Argh!

22:39.234 --> 22:41.566
Oh, right. Not Hullen.
Keep forgetting.

22:41.653 --> 22:42.984
Enough!

22:45.698 --> 22:49.031
l have had
a very trying day.

22:50.161 --> 22:54.871
Touch my family again,
and I will feed you
your own skin.

22:58.336 --> 23:01.703
and lwill put my foot
so far up your ass,

23:01.798 --> 23:04.881
you will taste
my ancestor's boots.

23:07.220 --> 23:08.551
Who's first?

23:10.890 --> 23:12.050
Thoughtso.

23:17.522 --> 23:18.932
That's my mom.

23:20.400 --> 23:22.482
WARDEN: I'll say this
forthe Killjoys.

23:22.860 --> 23:24.816
Never seen a crew
so dedicated to each other.

23:24.904 --> 23:26.064
JOHN: What do you mean?

23:27.282 --> 23:29.238
The only way I could keep
Yardeen in those fights

23:29.325 --> 23:30.735
was to promise to let you go.

23:33.079 --> 23:35.035
She was fighting
to get me off
the ship?

23:36.249 --> 23:37.705
You didn't know?

23:37.792 --> 23:39.748
NEWCY: Johnny?
Newcy?

23:39.836 --> 23:41.246
I’m in the mainframe.

23:41.337 --> 23:42.873
l have control
of the comms array,

23:42.964 --> 23:44.750
the loudspeaker system,
everything.

23:44.841 --> 23:46.502
Look!

23:46.593 --> 23:48.834
Okay. Easy there, girl.

23:50.930 --> 23:52.340
(DOOR OPENING)

23:54.434 --> 23:55.844
All right,
shouldn't be long.

23:55.935 --> 23:58.893
Just a slight delay.
All right, Captain Pike.

23:58.980 --> 24:00.720
Let's cut the
bullshit now,
shall we?

24:00.815 --> 24:04.023
I know the difference
between negotiating
and stalling for time,

24:04.110 --> 24:06.772
and you are definitely
doing the latter.
The only question is, why?

24:06.863 --> 24:09.696
What the hells are you doing?
You're screwing up my deal.

24:09.782 --> 24:10.897
Your deal?

24:10.992 --> 24:13.734
NEWCY:
Dutch, you’re in danger.
Lucy?

24:13.828 --> 24:15.864
How does ajunker
like this have Al?

24:15.955 --> 24:17.456
And who the shit is Dutch?

24:17.749 --> 24:20.081
Whoa, whoa,
everyone relax.

24:20.460 --> 24:22.667
NEWCY:
Since the situation
is deteriorating,

24:22.754 --> 24:24.836
John would
like me to inform you
that the Qreshi team

24:24.922 --> 24:26.958
is planting explosives
throughout the ship.

24:28.384 --> 24:30.921
We can still work this out.
Coren, you idiot.

24:31.012 --> 24:32.798
Don't you see
what's going on?

24:32.889 --> 24:34.299
They're not here
to save their people.

24:34.390 --> 24:36.802
They're here to
make sure their people
never get out alive.

24:36.893 --> 24:39.475
Well, give
the lady a prize.

24:40.146 --> 24:41.761
You cheating
rat bastard!

24:47.278 --> 24:49.189
Forget them!
They're dead anyway!

24:58.289 --> 25:00.871
(BOTH GRUNTING)

25:05.088 --> 25:06.419
Argh!

25:15.932 --> 25:17.888
DUTCH:
Mace, you don't
want to do this.

25:18.685 --> 25:20.300
Shoot, you stupid
piece of...
(GUN FIRES)

25:26.359 --> 25:28.224
Sparlo was
a son of a bitch.

25:29.445 --> 25:31.310
But he didn't deserve
to die like that.

25:35.368 --> 25:37.199
Then help me honor his memory.

25:39.997 --> 25:42.613
We always figured
we'd die on this ship.

25:43.626 --> 25:45.491
I'm still okay with that.
Good luck...

25:47.296 --> 25:48.627
Killjoy.

25:51.217 --> 25:52.582
Good luck, Mace.

25:55.888 --> 25:57.469
Okay, boys. Here I come.

26:00.393 --> 26:02.179
Coren? Mace?

26:03.271 --> 26:04.886
Is there anybody?
Fall over.

26:05.606 --> 26:07.437
Excuse me?
Sitting on the floor
is bad enough.

26:07.525 --> 26:08.890
I said fall over.

26:09.360 --> 26:10.896
Ooh!

26:12.488 --> 26:15.901
Hey, hey.
Something's wrong.
She's not breathing.

26:17.744 --> 26:20.201
Hey, come on, man.
You don't wanna lose
a hostage, do you?

26:36.053 --> 26:37.509
(BODY THUDS)

26:38.139 --> 26:39.595
Okay, we gotta figure out
what's going on.
(GUN COCKS)

26:39.682 --> 26:40.797
EVI: I'm gonna finish this.

26:40.892 --> 26:42.382
Now!

26:42.477 --> 26:44.092
Oh, come on!

27:05.708 --> 27:07.244
Put it down.
You first.

27:07.710 --> 27:08.950
She's on our side, Dutch.

27:10.213 --> 27:12.920
Okay, side-ish.
But we all want
the same thing,

27:13.007 --> 27:14.292
to get this ship
back from Coren.

27:14.383 --> 27:15.634
Coren's dead.

27:15.718 --> 27:17.583
Our biggest problem
is the Qreshi kill squad.

27:17.678 --> 27:19.464
Where the hells are they,
and where are their bombs?

27:19.555 --> 27:21.716
NEWCY: Johnny.
Yes, Newcy?

27:21.808 --> 27:25.676
l have identified three more
sites where the fusion
charges have been laid,

27:25.770 --> 27:30.264
but I’m also tracking five
individuals heading
directly to section 5-C.

27:30.358 --> 27:31.848
That's the personal
quarters area.

27:31.943 --> 27:33.479
If that's where D'av
and the Robbels are...

27:33.569 --> 27:35.855
I'll take care of the bombs.
You go save your friend.

27:35.947 --> 27:37.483
Why would you trust her?

27:37.573 --> 27:40.030
'Cause she hasn't
tried to kick me off
the ship, for one.

27:42.036 --> 27:43.867
Um, Johnny, maybe
this isn't the time.

27:43.955 --> 27:45.491
I didn't try
to kick you off.

27:45.581 --> 27:47.162
It was so you could get
a message out to Zeph.

27:47.250 --> 27:49.366
We're in a floating
satellite dish, Dutch.

27:49.460 --> 27:50.961
I think I'm pretty good
at hitting send.

27:51.045 --> 27:52.831
Okay, I'm gonna
go take care of
the bombs,

27:52.922 --> 27:54.583
but, as a former
psychiatrist,

27:54.674 --> 27:56.414
I suggest you two work
your shit out

27:56.509 --> 27:58.625
before your
friend dies.

28:00.471 --> 28:02.803
Do you know what you're
also really good at?

28:02.890 --> 28:04.426
Icing me out.

28:04.517 --> 28:05.723
Icing you?

28:05.810 --> 28:08.677
It hasn't exactly been easy
for me since we got
out of Old Town, Dutch.

28:09.230 --> 28:10.686
And it was for me?

28:11.440 --> 28:14.432
lwas there too, Johnny.
I remember us too.

28:15.319 --> 28:16.855
Did you ever ask me
how I felt?

28:19.949 --> 28:22.907
So, yeah, I did try
to send you away.

28:23.703 --> 28:25.785
Because whatever
you were going through,

28:26.205 --> 28:28.366
it was easier
to have you gone
than to have you here

28:28.457 --> 28:29.867
and not be my friend.

28:33.504 --> 28:37.713
Give me a sec.
Ijust got a message with
a weird encryption key.

28:37.800 --> 28:41.088
So you're a Killjoy?
That's right, honey.

28:41.178 --> 28:42.679
Maybe you could be
a Killjoy too.

28:43.514 --> 28:46.221
Whatever I do,
I'm pretty sure
I work for a living, son.

28:46.809 --> 28:49.596
Well, Zeph, he might
not know who he is,
but he's still an asshole.

28:49.687 --> 28:51.598
(GASPS)
You're proud of this?

28:51.689 --> 28:53.554
It's him! It's Johnny.

28:54.025 --> 28:55.140
He sent a message.

28:55.985 --> 28:59.398
They're alive on
the Herks Supermax
Prison Ship.

28:59.488 --> 29:01.319
Nice friends you have.
Shh!

29:01.657 --> 29:02.646
Okay.

29:03.618 --> 29:06.576
Coren Jeers,
gladiator fights... Cool.

29:06.662 --> 29:08.163
Anyway, they have a plan.

29:08.247 --> 29:09.953
When they get back,
we have to evacuate
Old Town.

29:10.041 --> 29:12.248
PREE OVER COMPUTER:
E vacuating a whole city
with no memory of its past...

29:12.335 --> 29:13.370
How hard can that be?

29:13.461 --> 29:15.122
Hey, wait.
What’s the last part?

29:15.713 --> 29:18.170
What? "Herks
has been hijacked.

29:18.257 --> 29:20.669
"Man y hostages,
Qreshis trying to
blow up the ship. "

29:20.968 --> 29:22.344
Gods.

29:28.809 --> 29:30.060
You don't
wanna do this, Evi.

29:30.144 --> 29:31.930
Oh, I really, really do.

29:32.021 --> 29:34.478
Okay, well...
You shouldn't.

29:35.024 --> 29:36.013
VVhy?

29:37.485 --> 29:39.225
Uh...
Oh, thank you very much.

29:39.320 --> 29:41.026
N EWCY:
Actual/y, D’a vin,
if it helps,

29:41.113 --> 29:44.071
there are three
Qreshi soldiers on
their way to kill all of you.

29:44.158 --> 29:46.149
Lucy?
"Newcy. "

29:46.243 --> 29:47.983
Why is the ship
talking to you?

29:48.079 --> 29:50.616
And what Qreshi soldiers
are coming to kill us?

29:51.082 --> 29:53.619
Members of Land Robbel’s
security force.

29:53.709 --> 29:54.824
What is wrong
with you people?

29:54.919 --> 29:56.875
Is anyone in your family
not trying to kill
each other?

29:56.963 --> 29:59.079
I'm sorry,
have you never
had a family dispute?

29:59.173 --> 30:02.006
Seriously.
I've never tried
to kill my brother!

30:03.344 --> 30:05.585
Intentionally.
Look, the point is...

30:05.680 --> 30:08.547
lfyou die,
I'm the next in line
of succession,

30:08.683 --> 30:09.923
if I get married.

30:10.017 --> 30:12.008
But if I die too...

30:12.770 --> 30:14.886
It stays with Uncle.
Mmm.

30:14.981 --> 30:16.096
See?

30:16.399 --> 30:17.935
You guys
don't have a problem
with each other.

30:18.025 --> 30:21.859
Your uncle is using
this opportunity
to kill you both.

30:21.946 --> 30:23.902
So why don't
you do something
completely crazy,

30:23.990 --> 30:26.948
